Annotated consensus SEG file expression density plots for loss calls

Chante Bethell for ALSF CCDL

2020

This notebook produces density plots using the z-scored expression values in the annotated consensus SEG files found in the results directory of this module. Note that the consensus SEG file does not have copy number information for sex chromosomes.

Set Up

Libraries and Functions

# Get `magrittr` pipe
`%>%` <- dplyr::`%>%`

The custom function below plots the density plots.

plot_density_expression <- function (cn_df,
                                     plotname_lead) {
  # Given a data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression data, produce a
  # stacked barplot for loss calls, neutral calls, and instances where
  # `copy_number` == 0.
  #
  # Args:
  #   cn_expression_loss_df: data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression
  #                          data produced using `merge_expression` custom
  #                          function and filtered for loss calls
  #   cn_expression_neutral_df: data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression
  #                             data produced using `merge_expression` custom
  #                             function and filtered for neutral calls
  #   cn_expression_zero_df: data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression
  #                          data produced using `merge_expression` custom
  #                          function and filtered for `copy_number` = 0
  #   plotname_lead: lead for name to save the combined stacked barplot as
  #
  # Returns:
  #   Plots density plot.
  

  # Change NA to `neutral`
  cn_df <- cn_df %>%
    dplyr::mutate(status = dplyr::case_when(is.na(status) ~ "neutral",
                                            TRUE ~ status))
  
  # Plot and save
  cn_expression_plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(cn_df,
                                        ggplot2::aes(x = z_score,
                                                     fill = status)) +
    ggplot2::geom_density(alpha = 0.2) +
    ggplot2::labs(title = toupper(paste0(plotname_lead, "_density_plot")))
  
  cn_expression_plot
}

plot_facetted_density_expression <- function (cn_df,
                                     plotname_lead) {
  # Given a data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression data, produce a
  # stacked barplot for loss calls, neutral calls, and instances where
  # `copy_number` == 0.
  #
  # Args:
  #   cn_expression_loss_df: data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression
  #                          data produced using `merge_expression` custom
  #                          function and filtered for loss calls
  #   cn_expression_neutral_df: data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression
  #                             data produced using `merge_expression` custom
  #                             function and filtered for neutral calls
  #   cn_expression_zero_df: data.frame with annotated CN and RNA expression
  #                          data produced using `merge_expression` custom
  #                          function and filtered for `copy_number` = 0
  #   plotname_lead: lead for name to save the combined stacked barplot as
  #
  # Returns:
  #   Plots factted density plots.
  

  # Change NA to `neutral`
  cn_df <- cn_df %>%
    dplyr::filter(gene_id %in% goi_list$V1) %>%
    dplyr::mutate(status = dplyr::case_when(is.na(status) ~ "neutral",
                                            TRUE ~ status))
  
  # Plot and save
  cn_expression_plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(cn_df,
                                        ggplot2::aes(x = z_score,
                                                     fill = status)) +
    ggplot2::geom_density(alpha = 0.4) +
    ggplot2::facet_wrap(~gene_id, ncol = 4) +
    ggplot2::labs(title = toupper(paste0(plotname_lead, "_density_plot")))
  
  cn_expression_plot
}

# Read in list of driver genes
goi_list <-
  read.delim(
    file.path(
      "..",
      "..",
      "analyses",
      "oncoprint-landscape",
      "driver-lists",
      "brain-goi-list-long.txt"
    ),
    sep = "\t",
    header = FALSE,
    as.is = TRUE
  )

Plot

Plot the annotated consensus SEG autosomes files.

plot_density_expression(consensus_autosome_stranded,
                        "consensus_seg_annotated_cn_autosomes_stranded")


plot_density_expression(consensus_autosome_polya,
                        "consensus_seg_annotated_cn_autosomes_polya")

Facet plot the annotated consensus SEG autosomes files.

plot_facetted_density_expression(consensus_autosome_stranded,
                        "consensus_seg_annotated_cn_autosomes_stranded")


plot_facetted_density_expression(consensus_autosome_polya,
                        "consensus_seg_annotated_cn_autosomes_polya")
